h1("4. Why Migrate to MassTransit")
bullets([
    "<b>One shared bus connection</b> instead of two independently-managed connections (publisher + consumer each opened their own).",
    "<b>Automatic retry &amp; error handling</b> &mdash; failed message processing can be retried with a backoff policy, and poison messages are moved to a "
    "<font face='Courier'>_error</font> queue instead of silently stalling consumption.",
    "<b>No manual queue/connection lifecycle code</b> &mdash; MassTransit registers its own IHostedService that starts/stops the bus with the app.",
    "<b>Strongly-typed consumers</b> (<font face='Courier'>IConsumer&lt;EmployeeEvent&gt;</font>) instead of parsing raw byte arrays.",
    "<b>Transport independence</b> &mdash; the same publish/consume code would work against Azure Service Bus or Amazon SQS if you ever changed transports.",
    "<b>Built-in test harness</b> (<font face='Courier'>MassTransit.TestFramework</font>) so consumers can be unit tested without a real broker.",
])

